on the bucks,

01:51.011 --> 01:53.309
and they turn on you.

01:53.447 --> 01:54.642
- Hey, Chachi.
- Hey, Rich.

01:54.781 --> 01:57.341
Hey, listen, uh...

01:57.484 --> 01:59.714
you seen Fonzie around?
I got a problem.

01:59.853 --> 02:01.446
Well, he's still out to lunch.
Why? What's up?

02:01.588 --> 02:03.386
Aw, Ralph went away
on his family reunion.

02:03.523 --> 02:05.423
I got to find a piano player.

02:05.559 --> 02:07.459
Hey, I'll do it for five bucks.

02:07.594 --> 02:09.756
- I didn't know you played.
- I don't.

02:09.895 --> 02:11.125
But I figured
I'd use two bucks for a date

02:11.264 --> 02:12.857
and the other three
for piano lessons.

02:13.000 --> 02:14.627
Pass. No, I'll pass.

02:15.636 --> 02:18.105
(rhythmic rattling)

02:18.238 --> 02:20.229
Hey, Fonz.

02:21.775 --> 02:23.300
Hey, this is Leilani.

02:23.443 --> 02:25.935
She works at the Pineapple Hut.

02:28.515 --> 02:30.108
(rattling)

02:32.886 --> 02:35.378
She just told you what
the special was for today.

02:35.522 --> 02:36.489
Oh, great.

02:36.623 --> 02:38.387
I'll have one to go.

02:39.793 --> 02:41.090
Uh, so, she doesn't talk?

02:41.228 --> 02:42.559
She don't have to.

02:42.696 --> 02:45.063
Saturday night,
Pineapple Hut, 8:00.

02:45.198 --> 02:46.666
(rattling)

02:46.800 --> 02:49.360
All right, all right,
all right! 7:30.

02:51.038 --> 02:52.028
- Oh, Fonz, listen.
- Yeah.

02:52.172 --> 02:53.298
Do you know a piano player?

02:53.440 --> 02:54.407
I got to find a piano player.

02:54.541 --> 02:56.168
Well, I-l know a piano teacher.

02:56.309 --> 02:57.174
Oh, yeah? Do you,
do you think she could play

02:57.310 --> 02:58.175
with our band Saturday night?

02:58.311 --> 02:59.210
No, Saturday night

02:59.346 --> 03:00.313
she's giving me a lesson

03:00.447 --> 03:02.506
in my key-

03:02.649 --> 03:04.014
Well, I don't know.
I'd better get going.

03:04.151 --> 03:05.846
I got this sudden urge
for pineapple.

03:05.986 --> 03:08.148
Bye, Richie.

03:09.423 --> 03:11.255
- Uh, Fonz?
- Yeah?

03:11.391 --> 03:12.881
Could I talk to you
for a minute?

03:13.026 --> 03:14.619
Oh, yeah, sure.
My ears are all yours.

03:14.761 --> 03:15.751
Conversate with me.

03:15.896 --> 03:17.864
Okay, uh,
I was talking to, um...

03:17.998 --> 03:19.830
- Fonz...?
- Speak up, speak up!

03:19.966 --> 03:21.092
All right.

03:21.234 --> 03:22.861
Fonz, can I talk
to you for a minute?!

03:23.904 --> 03:25.531
L-I'm sorry. It's important.

03:25.672 --> 03:27.231
It's important?
You got to tell me these things.

03:27.374 --> 03:28.967
- It's about Judy.
- Yeah, what about her?

03:29.109 --> 03:30.406
She wants to go to the movies.

03:30.544 --> 03:31.841
- Oh, that's good.
- But I don't have any money.

03:31.978 --> 03:33.639
- Oh, that's bad.
- I want a raise.

03:33.780 --> 03:35.145
- That's out.
- Oh...

03:35.282 --> 03:37.216
Fonz, you know how expensive
it is to take

03:37.350 --> 03:38.579
somebody to the movies
these days?

03:38.719 --> 03:40.710
Yeah, my dates
keep telling me that.

03:40.854 --> 03:42.583
Aw, come on, what's
a few more bucks a week?

03:42.723 --> 03:43.588
You know,
I'll tell you something.

03:43.724 --> 03:44.589
You don't get no raise, huh?

03:44.725 --> 03:45.590
Where's your get-up-and-go?

03:45.726 --> 03:46.591
This is America.

03:46.727 --> 03:48.559
Land of opportunities.

03:48.695 --> 03:49.685
"Opportunities"?

03:49.830 --> 03:52.060
What you mean is
another part-time job.

03:52.199 --> 03:54.827
You know what Grandma Nussbaum
always used to say?

03:54.968 --> 03:57.528
"A penny earned

03:57.671 --> 04:00.333
is a sailor's delight."

04:02.642 --> 04:05.976
I never did understand
Grandma Nussbaum.

04:06.113 --> 04:07.239
♪ Tonight's the night ♪

04:07.380 --> 04:09.348
♪ I came here
to rock and roll... ♪

04:09.483 --> 04:10.814
Well, we got to play tonight,
so let's just try

04:10.951 --> 04:12.749
-to think of a piano player.
- Yeah.

04:12.886 --> 04:14.081
Liberace. Ha-ha!

04:14.221 --> 04:15.950
- I still got it.
- Pots?

04:16.089 --> 04:17.921
Hey, Ralph's gone.
I thought I'd do the jokes.

04:18.058 --> 04:19.321
- Oh.
-(laughs)

04:19.459 --> 04:20.551
You all right, Al?

04:20.694 --> 04:22.788
Oh, I'm fine.
I always warm up like this

04:22.929 --> 04:26.058
before I do my piano exercises.

04:26.199 --> 04:27.530
- Well, there must be somebody.
- Yeah.

04:27.667 --> 04:28.862
Hey, you know,
I can play the piano

04:29.002 --> 04:30.299
but-but you'd need
another guitar player.

04:30.437 --> 04:31.734
- That's a good point.
- Yeah.

04:31.872 --> 04:33.431
Oh, Al, do you mind?

04:33.573 --> 04:34.904
We're trying
to concentrate here.

04:35.041 --> 04:36.839
Could you practice
the piano on another table?

04:36.977 --> 04:38.672
Bink.

04:38.812 --> 04:42.146
Hey, wait a minute.
Al could play the piano.

04:42.282 --> 04:45.513
Oh, I don't know.
I get so busy here.

04:45.652 --> 04:46.642
- Yeah, Al's right.
- Yeah, he'll get busy.

04:46.787 --> 04:49.017
I'll do it!

04:49.156 --> 04:51.056
Okay, everybody,
gather round.

04:51.191 --> 04:52.454
Come on, clear the table, folks.

04:52.592 --> 04:53.855
-(murmuring)
- RICHIE: Oh, hey, Chach.

04:53.994 --> 04:55.484
Let me introduce you

04:55.629 --> 04:59.156
to the most amazing miracle
product you'll ever see.

04:59.299 --> 05:02.758
Ladies and gentlemen,
this is lncredo-Wax.

05:02.903 --> 05:05.201
Oh, I'm sorry, Chach,
but I got all the wax I need.

05:05.338 --> 05:06.430
Hold it, Al.

05:06.573 --> 05:07.904
Let your eyes be the judge.

05:08.041 --> 05:10.806
I'll give you
a free demonstration.

05:10.944 --> 05:12.412
- All right, uh, let's see it.
- Yeah.

05:12.546 --> 05:14.947
(spritzing)

05:18.752 --> 05:21.585
And, folks, you're not going
to believe what you see next,

05:21.721 --> 05:23.314
even when you're seeing it.

05:27.460 --> 05:29.258
- Wow.
-(Potsie whistling)

05:29.396 --> 05:30.557
-(crowd oohing)
- Holy Moly.

05:30.697 --> 05:32.722
Don't hurt your eyes
from the glare, folks.

05:32.866 --> 05:34.630
Hey, man,
you could eat off this table.

05:34.768 --> 05:36.827
- Yeah, hey, Chach, let me have
one of those. -Terrific.

05:36.970 --> 05:39.132
-(excited chattering)
- Hey, Chachi, count me in.

05:39.272 --> 05:40.569
I think Mom would like
one of those, don't you?

05:40.707 --> 05:42.641
Yeah. Hey,
will it work on shoes?

05:42.776 --> 05:44.437
Certainly it works on shoes.

05:44.578 --> 05:45.773
Step right up, folks.

05:45.912 --> 05:47.402
Hurry, hurry, hurry-

05:47.547 --> 05:49.538
(excited chattering)

05:50.584 --> 05:53.053
HOWARD:
Marion?

05:56.857 --> 05:59.986
Marion? Marion!

06:00.126 --> 06:02.356
- Mar... oh!
- Oh!

06:02.495 --> 06:05.123
Do you have to pop up
at people like that?

06:05.265 --> 06:06.494
I'm sorry, dear.

06:06.633 --> 06:07.828
I was just looking
for my cookie sheet.

06:07.968 --> 06:10.096
Uh, is Joanie feeling better?

06:10.237 --> 06:11.966
Well, her temperature's down
and her complaints are up,

06:12.105 --> 06:13.334
so I guess she's better.

06:13.473 --> 06:15.202
- Oh, good.
-(loud clattering)

06:15.342 --> 06:16.537
Marion.

06:16.676 --> 06:18.940
You see, having the Andersons
over for bridge

06:19.079 --> 06:20.774
makes you so nervous, Howard.

06:20.914 --> 06:22.746
I am not nervous.

06:22.883 --> 06:24.647
Don't try that again, Marion.

06:24.784 --> 06:26.377
Whatever you say, dear.

06:26.519 --> 06:28.681
To the untrained eye,
I may seem to be nervous,

06:28.822 --> 06:30.688
but I'm really all psyched up,
Marion.

06:30.824 --> 06:32.656
I've got my brain on "go."

06:32.792 --> 06:34.317
And I feel mentally alert

06:34.461 --> 06:35.951
and that's going to give me
that competitive edge.

06:36.096 --> 06:37.393
I'll tell you something,
Marion.

06:37.530 --> 06:38.827
I feel like I have
the killer instinct.

06:38.965 --> 06:40.160
Marion, where are you?

06:40.300 --> 06:41.665
Mari... (yells)

06:41.801 --> 06:44.168
What are you trying
to do to me?

06:44.304 --> 06:45.294
- Hi, Mom.
- MARION: Oh, Richard,

06:45.438 --> 06:46.735
- Lori Beth. -HOWARD: Oh, hi.
- Hi.

06:46.873 --> 06:48.637
- We, uh waxed your card table.
- Oh.

06:48.775 --> 06:50.334
We used Chachi's wax.

06:50.477 --> 06:52.673
- It's really good stuff.
- Terrific.

06:52.812 --> 06:53.973
Uh.

06:54.114 --> 06:55.604
Oh, you do that well, Dad.

06:55.749 --> 06:58.275
No, no, I saw a guy on
Beat the <i>Clock</i> the other day

06:58.418 --> 07:00.580
and he couldn't open
a card table.

07:00.720 --> 07:04.918
Of course, he was wearing
boxing gloves and a blindfold.

07:05.058 --> 07:06.890
Howard, do you want a blindfold?

07:07.027 --> 07:10.053
No, I'd rather have
the boxing gloves, Marion.

07:10.196 --> 07:13.166
Wait a minute,
is this our old card table?

07:13.300 --> 07:15.564
Yep, we polished
the chairs, too.

07:15.702 --> 07:17.136
Well, it's just beautiful.

07:17.270 --> 07:19.534
It looks just like real Formica.

07:20.573 --> 07:22.803
- I'll get the cards.
- Okay.

07:22.943 --> 07:25.469
Uh, well, we're going to go
to Arnold's now, Dad.

07:25.612 --> 07:27.944
- No, no, no, no, just a minute,
you two. -RICHIE: What?

07:28.081 --> 07:30.345
Marion and I have to practice
our bridge signals,

07:30.483 --> 07:32.747
and I need you two to pretend
to be the Andersons.

07:32.886 --> 07:34.217
Sit, sit.

07:34.354 --> 07:37.085
Gonna practice your cheating,
huh, Dad?

07:37.223 --> 07:39.453
I do not cheat, Richard.

07:39.592 --> 07:42.391
The Andersons cheat, and you
have to fight fire with fire.

07:42.529 --> 07:46.056
Now, you'll be Mr. Anderson
and you'll be Mrs. Anderson.

07:46.199 --> 07:47.667
Oh, my, my. my-

07:47.801 --> 07:50.099
Oh, your house looks so lovely,
darling,

07:50.236 --> 07:52.398
and I just love those drapes.

07:52.539 --> 07:55.099
Well, thank you, Margaret, but
I've just had them for ages.

07:55.241 --> 07:56.902
Marion.

07:59.079 --> 08:02.777
Eh, uh, (exhales loudly)

08:02.916 --> 08:05.044
We're really going
to skin you tonight, Howie.

08:05.185 --> 08:06.516
(deep laugh)

08:06.653 --> 08:09.782
That's enough, Richard.

08:09.923 --> 08:12.153
Oh, I think it's cute, Howard.

08:12.292 --> 08:14.784
They sound just like
the Andersons.

08:14.928 --> 08:17.260
(laughs) Howie, how's that son
of yours doing, huh?

08:17.397 --> 08:19.092
Fine young boy.

08:20.300 --> 08:22.735
Smart-alecky as ever.

08:24.104 --> 08:25.503
Now, Marion, look at me.

08:25.638 --> 08:29.097
When you see me put my hand
over my heart,

08:29.242 --> 08:31.370
what does that mean?

08:31.511 --> 08:33.741
They're playing
the National Anthem.

08:35.381 --> 08:37.077
Oh, good one, Marion.
Good one.

08:37.217 --> 08:39.583
Oh, yeah, well, they always were
a funny couple.

08:39.719 --> 08:40.948
(Lori Beth cackles)

08:41.087 --> 08:42.179
I could tell you one time
Howie...

08:42.322 --> 08:44.484
You're pushing it, Richard.

08:45.925 --> 08:48.587
Marion, when I put my hand
over my heart,

08:48.728 --> 08:50.890
that means I have spades.

08:51.031 --> 08:52.726
Why doesn't it mean hearts?

08:52.866 --> 08:54.197
Because that's too obvious.

08:54.334 --> 08:55.893
You have to be clever.

08:56.036 --> 08:57.731
Howie, why don't you try
being really clever

08:57.871 --> 08:59.270
and learn to play bridge?

08:59.406 --> 09:01.773
LORI BETH (cackling):
Oh, my, good one, dear.

09:01.908 --> 09:04.502
Good one. (cackles)

09:04.644 --> 09:08.171
Pick up your cards,
we'll play a quick hand.

09:10.750 --> 09:12.548
LORI BETH: Hey, the cards
are stuck to the table.

09:12.685 --> 09:13.948
HOWARD:
What is this?

09:14.087 --> 09:17.148
Well, that's one way
to finally win, Howie.

09:17.290 --> 09:20.157
- Oh, Howard, now you've gone
too far. -|...

09:20.293 --> 09:22.455
I'm going to go in
and get a damp cloth.

09:22.595 --> 09:25.155
But I didn't...
What is...?

09:25.298 --> 09:28.461
Oh, Mom, I'll help you.
I...

09:28.601 --> 09:31.161
- Oh...
- Richie, I'm stuck.

09:31.304 --> 09:32.499
- I can't move.
- Richie.

09:32.639 --> 09:33.800
What is this?

09:33.940 --> 09:36.204
You know, uh, I saw a guy
on Beat the Clock...

09:36.342 --> 09:37.639
Richard!

09:37.777 --> 09:40.405
Margaret, when I walk around
with my chair like this,

09:40.547 --> 09:42.515
it means I have spades.

09:42.649 --> 09:43.980
MARION: Oh!

09:51.257 --> 09:53.248
(Al coughing)

09:54.594 --> 09:57.427
Chachi, Chachi, Chachi.

09:59.632 --> 10:00.827
(coin jingling)

10:01.868 --> 10:04.303
Al, Al, where is that Chachi?

10:04.437 --> 10:06.098
I'm trying to get him
on the phone right now.

10:06.239 --> 10:09.334
Good. I waxed
my new saddle shoes.

10:09.476 --> 10:11.410
Look at them.

10:11.544 --> 10:13.069
Oh, he's not answering.

10:13.213 --> 10:16.012
He probably waxed his phone.

10:17.050 --> 10:19.417
Hey, Lori Beth, Al,
look at this.

10:21.821 --> 10:23.220
LORI BETH: What is it?

10:23.356 --> 10:24.983
Before I used Chachi's wax
on it,

10:25.125 --> 10:27.685
it was my bowling ball.

10:27.827 --> 10:29.124
POTSIE (calling):
ls Jennifer in there?!

10:29.262 --> 10:30.593
- No.
- No.

10:30.730 --> 10:32.027
POTSIE:
Are you sure?

10:32.165 --> 10:33.223
- Yes.
- Yes.

10:33.366 --> 10:35.698
Potsie, come on out here.

10:37.000 --> 10:43.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

10:52.452 --> 10:55.183
RICHIE, LORI BETH & AL:
You put it on your hair.

10:55.321 --> 10:57.551
Where is he?
Where is that little twerp?

10:57.690 --> 10:59.055
I don't know-- look what
he did to my shoes.

10:59.192 --> 11:00.921
-(overlapping talking)
- The table-- look at the table.

11:01.060 --> 11:03.859
- Oh, my.
- Totally burnt out.

11:03.997 --> 11:06.295
(overlapping talking
continues)

11:06.432 --> 11:07.524
Hi, everybody.

11:07.667 --> 11:08.896
How'd the wax work?

11:10.370 --> 11:11.860
Bye. everybody.

11:12.005 --> 11:13.302
POTSIE:
Let's get him!

11:13.439 --> 11:14.964
AL:
Stop that boy!

11:26.786 --> 11:29.255
♪ I'm gonna look so sweet ♪

11:29.389 --> 11:32.256
♪ On my bicycle seat ♪

11:32.392 --> 11:34.486
♪ Built for one. ♪

11:36.529 --> 11:38.156
- Fonz.
- Hey, Richie.

11:38.298 --> 11:39.561
Where's Chachi?

11:39.699 --> 11:41.497
What do I look like,
my cousin's keeper?

11:41.634 --> 11:43.124
Just wait
till I get my hands on him.

11:43.269 --> 11:44.361
I mean, Fonz, I'm telling you.

11:44.504 --> 11:45.733
Just wait till
I get my hands on him.

11:45.872 --> 11:47.340
All right, slow down,
you're gonna bust something.

11:47.473 --> 11:49.305
- Now, what's up?
- He's ruined everything.

11:49.442 --> 11:52.070
I mean, my bowling ball...
(makes warbling sound)

11:52.212 --> 11:53.373
My father's card table,

11:53.513 --> 11:55.003
Lori Beth's shoes,
Potsie's hair.

11:55.148 --> 11:57.014
I mean, you should just see
Potsie's hair.

11:57.150 --> 11:59.016
I tell you,
I'm gonna get Chachi.

11:59.152 --> 12:01.484
All right, hey, look,
get him later-- talk now.

12:11.397 --> 12:12.865
-(snapping fingers)
- Hey, are you home?

12:12.999 --> 12:15.593
Oh, yeah, Fonz. Uh...

12:15.735 --> 12:17.533
Chachi's selling stuff.

12:17.670 --> 12:18.535
Yeah, I know that.

12:18.671 --> 12:19.638
It's called lncredo-Wax.

12:19.772 --> 12:20.796
I bought some.

12:20.940 --> 12:22.806
Yeah, I thought so.

12:22.942 --> 12:24.967
Shined up my seat.

12:25.111 --> 12:27.409
I can see that.

12:27.547 --> 12:29.208
I like to encourage the kid

12:29.349 --> 12:31.317
when he shows
some get-up-and-go.

12:31.451 --> 12:34.250
That's not all
that's getting up and going.

12:38.825 --> 12:40.020
All right...

12:41.060 --> 12:43.427
Now, Fonz, Fonz,
just-just take it easy.

12:43.563 --> 12:45.793
I mean, it's only your
motorcycle seat, right?

12:45.932 --> 12:48.424
Did you say "only"
about my motorcycle?

12:48.568 --> 12:50.263
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.
Look, I'm mad, too, Fonz,

12:50.403 --> 12:51.598
but you said it yourself,

12:51.738 --> 12:53.069
the kid's trying to make
some extra cash.

12:53.206 --> 12:54.230
He's a businessman.

12:54.374 --> 12:56.001
Hey, I'm gonna give him
the business.

12:56.142 --> 12:58.611
Fonz, just take it easy.
He's only 16.

12:58.745 --> 13:00.611
This thing is going
to float away.

13:00.747 --> 13:03.239
And besides, the way I saw him
running out of Arnold's,

13:03.383 --> 13:05.147
I don't think you're going
to find him for a while.

13:05.285 --> 13:07.253
I know how to find him.

13:09.956 --> 13:13.722
This is going to hurt me
more than it hurts you.

13:18.531 --> 13:22.024
Fonz, you're taking it well.

13:23.569 --> 13:25.663
(frustrated growling)

13:33.379 --> 13:35.848
Let's go and get him.

