he'll be here.

15:58.958 --> 16:02.189
Four, three, two, one.

16:02.328 --> 16:03.386
(Snap fingers)

16:03.529 --> 16:04.792
- Oh, I love papaya.
-(rhythmic rattling)

16:04.931 --> 16:06.626
I love pineapple,
all that South Seas stuff.

16:06.766 --> 16:08.564
Now, look,
why don't you and me...

16:11.971 --> 16:13.632
This is an ambush, huh?

16:14.574 --> 16:17.043
Does this mean the luau's off?

16:17.176 --> 16:18.974
-(snaps fingers) -All right,
in my office, right now.

16:19.111 --> 16:21.375
Eh... boy.

16:21.514 --> 16:22.879
What are you complaining about?

16:23.015 --> 16:24.380
It looks terrific.

16:28.054 --> 16:29.647
Fonz, are you sure
that you want to...

16:29.789 --> 16:30.813
- You, too.
- Me?

16:30.957 --> 16:33.790
- Yeah.
- Ah.

16:33.926 --> 16:35.394
Fonz...

16:35.528 --> 16:36.620
Put your hat back on.

16:36.762 --> 16:38.696
Right, right.

16:39.899 --> 16:43.062
Hey, uh, I forgot what brunch
was on Sunday.

16:43.202 --> 16:46.001
(rattling)

16:46.138 --> 16:48.971
Thanks a lot.
I'll be there.

16:49.108 --> 16:51.099
Hey, I'm sorry, Judy,
I can't make it right now.

16:51.244 --> 16:53.406
I have a very important meeting
in my office.

16:53.546 --> 16:55.412
He'll call you back.

16:55.548 --> 16:57.846
And second of all,
this is my office.

16:57.984 --> 17:00.681
So, the killer of motorcycle
seats returns.

17:00.820 --> 17:02.219
How did I know the wax was bad?

17:02.355 --> 17:03.481
All right, let's sit down
and talk this out.

17:03.623 --> 17:04.988
Watch it, Richie, huh?

17:05.124 --> 17:07.183
All you're interested in doing
is making extra bucks, huh?

17:07.326 --> 17:08.487
That's right. You were the one
who told me

17:08.627 --> 17:09.857
to go out and earn
some extra money, right?

17:09.996 --> 17:11.828
- We'll stand up and talk.
- Richie, please, huh?

17:11.964 --> 17:13.329
I told you to earn
some extra money.

17:13.465 --> 17:15.434
I didn't tell you to ruin
Milwaukee in the process.

17:15.568 --> 17:17.468
I'm so inadequate when it comes
to confrontations.

17:17.603 --> 17:18.968
Richie, will you please.

17:19.105 --> 17:21.267
You know, I asked you for help,
but what'd you give me?

17:21.406 --> 17:23.603
Advice. Big deal.

17:23.742 --> 17:25.233
You know what I'm gonna do
from now on?

17:25.377 --> 17:27.368
Tell me.

17:41.227 --> 17:44.527
Fonz, everybody hates me.

17:44.664 --> 17:46.894
I need help.

17:51.604 --> 17:53.333
The kid needs help.

17:53.472 --> 17:55.236
What are you yelling
at him for, Rich?

17:56.275 --> 17:57.902
No, but, Fonz, I was the one...

17:58.044 --> 17:59.170
Hey, Richie,
I'll ask you a question.

17:59.312 --> 18:00.370
You remember when you were
16 years old?

18:00.513 --> 18:01.571
A little sensitivity, here.

18:01.714 --> 18:03.113
Yeah, uh, right, Fonz.

18:03.249 --> 18:06.275
All right, I'm such a sucker
when he gets humble.

18:06.419 --> 18:08.046
What happened?

18:08.187 --> 18:09.450
I don't know.

18:09.589 --> 18:11.580
Some shady looking guy said
I could make some big money.

18:11.724 --> 18:12.850
And then he dumps this wax

18:12.992 --> 18:14.482
that eats favorite things
on you, huh?

18:14.627 --> 18:16.026
You know what that
sounds like to me?

18:16.162 --> 18:18.290
- Richie, please.
- Then why am I here?

18:18.431 --> 18:21.628
- You're setting a good example.
- Ah...

18:21.767 --> 18:24.566
All right, now,
this is a typical con game.

18:24.704 --> 18:26.001
What's the guy's name?

18:26.138 --> 18:27.299
Uh, Becket.

18:27.440 --> 18:28.464
-(snaps fingers)
- Remember that.

18:28.608 --> 18:30.133
All right now,
he hustles kids, right?

18:30.276 --> 18:31.835
Dumps useless wax on them

18:31.978 --> 18:34.106
and then takes the money
and skedaddles.

18:34.246 --> 18:35.611
Not nice.

18:35.748 --> 18:37.978
See that?
What a lovely example.

18:38.117 --> 18:39.744
Fonz, what am I going to do?

18:39.885 --> 18:40.852
All right, you're gonna sit
right down here,

18:40.987 --> 18:42.716
take a load off your feet,

18:42.855 --> 18:44.584
don't slip into the sink.

18:44.724 --> 18:45.850
(Snaps fingers)

18:45.992 --> 18:47.790
- This con-er...
- Mm-hmm.

18:47.927 --> 18:49.361
...is going to become
our con-ee, huh?

18:49.495 --> 18:51.486
Here's what we're gonna do.

18:57.303 --> 18:58.862
So, what makes you think
this Becket guy

18:59.005 --> 19:00.097
is really going to show up?

19:00.239 --> 19:01.729
Greed, Red, greed.

19:01.874 --> 19:03.273
They're ain't enough money in
the world for guys like that.

19:03.409 --> 19:05.844
He thinks he's taking us
as easy marks, huh.

19:05.978 --> 19:07.912
Fonz, Fonz,
Becket just drove up.

19:08.047 --> 19:09.242
-(snaps fingers)
- All right, disappear.

19:09.382 --> 19:10.975
- Where? Where?
- My office. My office.

19:11.117 --> 19:13.643
Hurry. Hurry.

19:13.786 --> 19:15.754
Okay, okay, we're ready to go.

19:15.888 --> 19:16.980
(clears throat)

19:17.123 --> 19:19.751
Well, we're in...
we're in good now.

19:19.892 --> 19:21.417
All we gotta do is lay our hands
on that wax,

19:21.560 --> 19:23.426
then we close the deal
and we got ourselves

19:23.562 --> 19:24.893
half a million bucks.

19:25.031 --> 19:27.898
What about that sharpie,
you know, Mr. Becket?

19:28.034 --> 19:30.162
RICHIE: Oh, Beckefs a boob,
he won't know anything.

19:30.302 --> 19:31.497
The boob knows.

19:31.637 --> 19:34.129
Uh-oh. I think he heard.

19:34.273 --> 19:36.765
You're-you're, uh, Becket?

19:36.909 --> 19:38.138
You've got it.

19:38.277 --> 19:40.211
What's the scam
on a half a million?

19:40.346 --> 19:41.745
Half a million dollars?

19:41.881 --> 19:43.110
I never said anything
about a half a mill...

19:43.249 --> 19:44.444
Did you ever say anything
about a half a million?

19:44.583 --> 19:46.176
No. I can't even wrap my tongue
around those words.

19:46.318 --> 19:47.444
All right, stop the double-talk.

19:47.586 --> 19:50.146
You two got something big going
with my wax,

19:50.289 --> 19:52.314
and I want to know what it is.

19:52.458 --> 19:53.857
- All right, he's-he's got us,
Fonzarelli. -Yeah.

19:53.993 --> 19:56.257
Without his wax,
why, there's no deal.

19:56.395 --> 19:58.830
- I feel like a rat in a trap.
- Yeah.

19:58.964 --> 20:00.591
(rhythmic drumbeat, rattling)

20:00.733 --> 20:02.633
-(snaps fingers)
- Not now.

20:06.639 --> 20:09.870
Uh, you know,
the neighborhood's changing.

20:10.009 --> 20:12.103
Cut the clowning.
Now, what's the deal?

20:12.244 --> 20:14.269
Uh, I don't like violence, sir.

20:14.413 --> 20:16.643
All right, all right,
a kid sold us

20:16.782 --> 20:18.443
some of your lncredo-Wax, see,
and then, uh,

20:18.584 --> 20:20.211
and then my partner, Fonzie,
mixed it with something else,

20:20.352 --> 20:21.717
-another ingredient...
- BECKET: And-and what?

20:21.854 --> 20:23.049
- What, what?
- Well, it changed.

20:23.189 --> 20:24.179
Well, what did it change to?

20:24.323 --> 20:25.722
Well, show him, show him, Red.

20:25.858 --> 20:26.916
- Yeah, show me, come on.
- Yeah. All right.

20:27.059 --> 20:28.925
- I want to see this.
- Show him.

20:29.061 --> 20:30.654
- Ready, Fonzarelli?
- All right. Yeah, yeah.

20:31.697 --> 20:33.062
(metallic clang,
Fonzie grunts quietly)

20:33.199 --> 20:34.963
Hmm?

20:35.101 --> 20:36.694
Now, two hours ago,

20:36.836 --> 20:39.737
this was a flimsy piece
of cheap leather.

20:39.872 --> 20:42.933
And...
No, no, it was good leather.

20:43.075 --> 20:45.601
See, and then
we rubbed the wax on it.

20:45.745 --> 20:48.180
Yeah, and it became hard
as steel.

20:48.314 --> 20:49.543
(metallic clang)

20:49.682 --> 20:52.208
You two seem to have something
pretty good going here.

20:52.351 --> 20:54.080
I want in.

20:54.220 --> 20:55.847
All right.
Okay, how about this?

20:55.988 --> 20:58.150
- We'll cut you in for a third.
- Third.

20:58.290 --> 21:00.122
- I want half.
- Oh, man.

21:00.259 --> 21:01.658
- Unbelievable, unbelievable.
- Oh.

21:01.794 --> 21:03.262
All right, okay, we're going
to have to talk this over.

21:03.395 --> 21:04.726
- Talk it over. Make it quick.
- Okay.

21:04.864 --> 21:05.888
All right,
we're talking it over here.

21:06.031 --> 21:09.092
Look at us.
Here we are talking it over.

21:10.469 --> 21:12.267
Fonz, is your chest all right?

21:12.404 --> 21:14.566
Yeah, I think you bent my
favorite hubcap though.

21:14.707 --> 21:16.505
- Come on, snap it up,
snap it up. -(snapping fingers)

21:16.642 --> 21:18.736
- All right. -Meek is killing me,
you know that.

21:18.878 --> 21:20.004
I understand.

21:20.146 --> 21:21.477
BECKET: Snap it up.

21:21.614 --> 21:23.207
All right, all right.
We talked it over.

21:23.349 --> 21:25.647
We don't like it,
but you're in for half.

21:25.785 --> 21:27.617
- Whoa.
- That's fabulous.

21:27.753 --> 21:31.485
Now, partners, who's putting up
the half a million?

21:31.624 --> 21:32.648
Foreign interests.

21:32.792 --> 21:33.816
I don't like it.

21:33.959 --> 21:35.586
He pays it all in cash.

21:35.728 --> 21:37.526
-(ahooga horn blows)
- That's better.

21:37.663 --> 21:39.893
-(car door opens)
- There's his foreign car now.

21:40.032 --> 21:42.694
-(car door closes)
- Don't blow this deal.

21:42.835 --> 21:44.997
Ah...

21:48.274 --> 21:50.766
Greetings from the desert.

21:52.111 --> 21:56.207
May your camel always
stand upwind.

21:56.348 --> 21:58.544
YEP, YEP, YEP, YEP-

21:59.518 --> 22:00.883
Who is this infidel?

22:01.020 --> 22:02.545
Oh, no, we're very honored

22:02.688 --> 22:04.713
to have the inventor
of lncredo-Wax with us.

22:04.857 --> 22:06.757
Do you have the money?

22:06.892 --> 22:07.984
(Al laughs)

22:08.127 --> 22:09.822
Foreign suitcase.

22:09.962 --> 22:12.124
Yankee dollars.

22:12.264 --> 22:14.130
Uh, uh, uh, uh.

22:14.266 --> 22:15.791
First demonstration.

22:15.935 --> 22:17.960
- Oh, right, we promised
a demonstration. -Yeah.

22:18.103 --> 22:19.537
Hey, uh, put it on the car.

22:19.672 --> 22:20.696
I don't think
you should do that.

22:20.840 --> 22:22.239
Well, it'll make it dent-proof,
you know.

22:22.374 --> 22:23.671
Well, no, I'm not so sure now.

22:23.809 --> 22:26.301
Hey, I know what I'm doing.

22:26.445 --> 22:28.243
Yeah, hey, whatever you want,
whatever you want.

22:28.380 --> 22:29.745
Here, some lncredo-Wax.

22:29.882 --> 22:30.974
There you go.

22:31.116 --> 22:33.448
- You'll love the demonstration.
-(Al laughs)

22:33.586 --> 22:36.783
If this works,
my camels will be invincible.

22:39.859 --> 22:42.590
Here, that ought to be hard
enough now.

22:42.728 --> 22:46.096
You, hood,
hand me a sledgehammer.

22:53.172 --> 22:55.800
Your Sheikhness, dig this.

22:55.941 --> 22:57.670
(loud clanging)

22:59.245 --> 23:00.440
Maybe the fender'll be harder.

23:00.579 --> 23:01.910
I can try the fender.
Watch this.

23:02.047 --> 23:03.481
This is going to be good
for you.

23:03.616 --> 23:05.607
(loud clanging)

23:12.625 --> 23:14.115
Wait, wait, wait.

23:14.260 --> 23:15.989
No, no, no, no.
No handcuffs.

23:16.128 --> 23:18.825
Give me his hands.
Give me his hands.

23:28.841 --> 23:31.606
Hooray, we did it.

23:31.744 --> 23:35.408
AL, FONZIE & RICHIE:
Chachi, Chachi, Chachi.

23:43.756 --> 23:45.417
Boy, I worked out
a terrific deal with Al.

23:45.557 --> 23:47.218
I work for seven weeks
